Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @dried rigatoni{180%grams}.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%grams}(halved).

Place a medium #pan{} over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%grams} for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the tomatoes and garlic. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened.

Add the @green pesto{1%sachet}, @creme fraiche{125%grams} and half the @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams} to the pan.

Add the pasta and stir to coat. Turn off the heat and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the pasta between plates or bowls.

Garnish with the remaining cheese.